   "source": [
    "# Toegang tot verkoelende plekken in Amsterdam\n",
    "### Individuele opdracht – Designing Future Cities\n",
    "#### V2: Robustere versie met betere error handling\n",
    "\n",
    "**Onderzoeksvraag:**  \n",
    "Welke inwoners van Amsterdam hebben binnen 5, 10 en 15 minuten lopen toegang tot verkoelende openbare ruimtes, en waar zijn de tekorten het grootst?\n",
    "\n",
    "**Methode:**\n",
    "1. Verkoelende plekken ophalen via OpenStreetMap (parken > 1ha, water > 5ha)\n",
    "2. Wandelnetwerk ophalen via OSMnx\n",
    "3. Isochrones berekenen (5/10/15 min) vanuit verkoelende plekken\n",
    "4. CBS bevolkingsdata koppelen\n",
    "5. Risicogebieden visualiseren\n",
    "\n",
    "**Definitie verkoeling:**  \n",
    "Openbare groengebieden > 1 hectare en wateroppervlakken > 5 hectare, op basis van thermisch verkoelend effect via verdamping en schaduw (OSM tags: `leisure=park`, `landuse=forest/grass`, `natural=water`)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Stap 0 – Libraries importeren"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import osmnx as ox\n",
    "import networkx as nx\n",
    "import geopandas as gpd\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.patches as mpatches\n",
    "from shapely.geometry import Point, MultiPolygon\n",
    "from shapely.ops import unary_union\n",
    "import contextily as ctx\n",
    "from tqdm import tqdm\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Reproduceerbaar + nette output\n",
    "ox.settings.log_console = False\n",
    "print(\"Libraries geladen ✓\")\n",
    "print(f\"OSMnx versie: {ox.__version__}\")\n",
    "print(f\"GeoPandas versie: {gpd.__version__}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Stap 1 – Verkoelende plekken ophalen via OSM\n",
    "\n",
    "We halen drie categorieën op:\n",
    "- **Parken** (`leisure=park`)\n",
    "- **Groengebieden** (`landuse=forest` of `landuse=grass`)\n",
    "- **Water** (`natural=water`)\n",
    "\n",
    "Daarna filteren we op minimale oppervlakte."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "CITY = \"Amsterdam, Netherlands\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Minimale oppervlaktes (in m²)\n",
    "MIN_PARK_M2  = 10_000   # 1 hectare\n",
    "MIN_WATER_M2 = 50_000   # 5 hectare\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Verkoelende plekken ophalen via OSM...\")\n",
    "print(f\"Criteria: parken >= {MIN_PARK_M2/10000:.0f} ha, water >= {MIN_WATER_M2/10000:.0f} ha\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- Parken ---\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    parks_raw = ox.features_from_place(CITY, tags={\"leisure\": \"park\"})\n",
    "    parks = parks_raw[parks_raw.geometry.type.isin([\"Polygon\", \"MultiPolygon\"])].copy()\n",
    "    parks = parks.to_crs(epsg=28992)  # RD New (meters) voor oppervlakteberekening\n",
    "    parks[\"area_m2\"] = parks.geometry.area\n",
    "    parks = parks[parks[\"area_m2\"] >= MIN_PARK_M2]\n",
    "    parks[\"type\"] = \"park\"\n",
    "    print(f\"✓ Parken gevonden: {len(parks)}\")\n",
    "except Exception as e:\n",
    "    print(f\"✗ Fout bij parken ophalen: {e}\")\n",
    "    parks = gpd.GeoDataFrame(columns=[\"geometry\", \"area_m2\", \"type\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- Groengebieden (bos/gras) ---\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    green_raw = ox.features_from_place(CITY, tags={\"landuse\": [\"forest\", \"grass\"]})\n",
    "    green = green_raw[green_raw.geometry.type.isin([\"Polygon\", \"MultiPolygon\"])].copy()\n",
    "    green = green.to_crs(epsg=28992)\n",
    "    green[\"area_m2\"] = green.geometry.area\n",
    "    green = green[green[\"area_m2\"] >= MIN_PARK_M2]\n",
    "    green[\"type\"] = \"groen\"\n",
    "    print(f\"✓ Groengebieden gevonden: {len(green)}\")\n",
    "except Exception as e:\n",
    "    print(f\"✗ Fout bij groen ophalen: {e}\")\n",
    "    green = gpd.GeoDataFrame(columns=[\"geometry\", \"area_m2\", \"type\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- Water ---\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    water_raw = ox.features_from_place(CITY, tags={\"natural\": \"water\"})\n",
    "    water = water_raw[water_raw.geometry.type.isin([\"Polygon\", \"MultiPolygon\"])].copy()\n",
    "    water = water.to_crs(epsg=28992)\n",
    "    water[\"area_m2\"] = water.geometry.area\n",
    "    water = water[water[\"area_m2\"] >= MIN_WATER_M2]\n",
    "    water[\"type\"] = \"water\"\n",
    "    print(f\"✓ Wateroppervlakken gevonden: {len(water)}\")\n",
    "except Exception as e:\n",
    "    print(f\"✗ Fout bij water ophalen: {e}\")\n",
    "    water = gpd.GeoDataFrame(columns=[\"geometry\", \"area_m2\", \"type\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Samenvoegen\n",
    "cols = [\"geometry\", \"area_m2\", \"type\"]\n",
    "cooling = pd.concat([\n",
    "    parks[cols] if len(parks) > 0 else pd.DataFrame(),\n",
    "    green[cols] if len(green) > 0 else pd.DataFrame(),\n",
    "    water[cols] if len(water) > 0 else pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "], ignore_index=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "if len(cooling) == 0:\n",
    "    raise ValueError(\"Geen verkoelende plekken gevonden! Check je internet/OSM.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "cooling = gpd.GeoDataFrame(cooling, crs=\"EPSG:28992\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(f\"Totaal verkoelende plekken: {len(cooling)}\")\n",
    "print(cooling[\"type\"].value_counts())"
   ]
  },
